$ WAVEWATCH III grid preprocessor for the Ripple duration-limited comparison.
$ Single-point homogeneous deep-water domain (3x3 mask trick), matches Ripple
$ spectral grid: 25 logarithmic frequency bins (XFR=1.1, f0=0.04118 Hz) × 24
$ directions.
$
  'Ripple duration test'
$
$ XFR, f0, NFR, NDIR, RTHETA
  1.10  0.04118  25  24  0.
$
$ Run flags: FLDRY FLCX FLCY FLCTH FLCK FLSOU
   F F F F F T
$
$ Time steps: global, x/y CFL, intra-spectral CFL, source-term min
  600.  600.  600. 15.
$
  &MISC FLAGTR = 0 /
END OF NAMELISTS
$
$ Rectangular grid, 3×3, trivial mask
$ 'TYPE'  FLAG  'NONE'
  'RECT' T 'NONE'
$ NX  NY
   3   3
$ SX (deg or m)  SY (deg or m)  unit-scale
   1.  1.  1.E-2
$ X0  Y0  Z-scale
  -1. -1.  1.E-2
$
$ Bathymetry: pretend 2500 m deep everywhere — “deep water”
  -5.  5.75  10  -2500. 3 1 '(....)' 'UNIT' 'input'
$
   1  1  1
   1  1  1
   1  1  1
$
$ Mask: all active
  10  1 1 '(....)' 'PART' 'input'
$
   0  0  F
   0  0  F
   0  0
$
$ Obstruction grid (none)
   0. 0. 0. 0.  0
$
$ Output point list (one point at the grid center)
   0.   0.   'point01'
   0.   0.   'STOPSTRING'
$
$ End.
